				<div class="elementor-widget-container">
							<p>Narula Institute of Technology (NIT), established in 2001 in Agarpara, Kolkata, under the JIS Group Educational Initiative, is a leading autonomous Engineering and Management Institute. Affiliated with MAKAUT, WB, and approved by AICTE, NIT has achieved NIRF Innovation rankings in 2023 and consistent NIRF rankings from 2017 to 2022. The Institute offers NBA-accredited B.Tech, M.Tech, BBA, BBA(HM), and BCA-MCA programs, with diploma courses affiliated under WBSCT&VE&SD, and has received NAAC 'A' accreditation. Recognized under UGC Act clauses 2(f) and 12(b) and awarded the TEQIP (phase 2) grant, NIT also mentors other institutions under the MoE’s Innovation Cell and received a 3.5-star rating in the IIC academic calendar 2022-23. NIT's robust R&D cell, supported by esteemed faculty and funding from UGC, DAE-BRNS, ISRO, AICTE, houses the JIS Bosch-Rexroth Centre of Excellence and Blue Star "Centre of Excellence," alongside advanced Language Laboratories.</p><p>Collaborations with corporate giants like Tech Mahindra, Reliance JIO, Oracle, and academic institutions like NIT Sikkim and IIT-KGP enrich student exposure through seminars, workshops, and field training. With active student chapters in various departments, students excel in technical and cultural fields, winning awards and participating in charitable activities. NIT fosters a ragging-free, supportive campus environment with a dedicated Women's Cell, modern teaching-learning processes, and a successful alumni network. The Institute’s focus on holistic development ensures students achieve placements with top MNCs such as Accenture, Infosys, TCS, Capgemini, Wipro, IBM, and more.</p>						</div>
